                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1"><P><B></B> <I>Database Processing, 9/E</I> provides a solid, modern foundation in the fundamentals of database processing. This new edition proves to be the most comprehensive revision of the book yet, with expanded and updated treatment of cutting-edge technologies like XML and ADO.NET. <B></B> ADO.NET, SQL, SQL Server, XML, Oracle, the entity-relationship model, database management, database redesign. <B></B> For database administrators, database designers, application programmers, or other professionals in the field who want a complete, up-to-date, easy-to-use database book.   </P></span>
              
</td></tr></table>
